review_blob: Quite a hoppy aroma backed up by light amber appearance and strong taste. Always an enjoyable pint.
Ah Blond Witch. An all round good beer with a slightly floral hint to it. Drinks very easily; very very easily.
Flavour quite yeasty. Fizzy (over fizzy), and a bit tacky on the mouth. Plus points - wet.
Surprisingly refreshing; quite a light option which does the job in humid environments.
